roadmap 232 done "[Pilot-T1 v3 launcher hardening — server-side daemonize + heartbeat marker + idle auto-kill + client-side polling fail-fast, post-$7.52 burn] anima-tribev2-pilot/scripts/launch_h100_pilot_t1_v3.sh.txt + anima-tribev2-pilot/docs/launcher_hardening_v3_design.md + anima-tribev2-pilot/state/markers/launcher_hardening_v3_complete.marker. **4 fixes**: (FIX-1) server-side daemonize via nohup + disown for run_install.sh and run_infer.sh — SSH drop decoupled from job survival. (FIX-2) heartbeat markers — install_started/install_done/inference_started/inference_done with timestamp+pid+rc on pod-side, pulled back to state/markers_pod_v3/ for offline forensic reconstruction. (FIX-3) idle auto-kill — pod-side watchdog.sh self-terminate (runpodctl stop pod || poweroff fallback) at IDLE_KILL_SEC=1800s if install_started.marker missing, caps worst-case idle burn at ~$1.50 (5× lower than v2's $7.52). (FIX-4) client-side polling — 30s short-lived ssh probes, distinct fail-fast budgets (install_started ≤ 1h / install_done ≤ 20m / inference_started ≤ 5m / inference_done ≤ INFER_CAP+2m), any breach → runpodctl stop pod from local. **DRY_RUN selftest**: positive 4/4 phases observed (install_started 1s / install_done 2s / inference_started 3s / inference_done 5s) + negative fail-fast 5s threshold triggered as expected. 2 repeat runs both PASS, deterministic. **byte-identical**: launcher sha256=6155c45d48dd66339727105ca6f6848a11b14bc25d150120d8c22f40720fadff, design sha256=868d73921d34c10c6ba697443b8701a8a9f76ee35d43a3a3471c86508ed20e89. **constraints honored**: v1+v2 launcher untouched (read-only), git commit X, GPU 0, $0. **burn-prevention verdict**: $7.52-class re-occurrence requires all 4 independent mechanisms to fail simultaneously."
  track          pilot-t1-launcher-hardening
  phase          v3-design-implement-selftest
  status         done (2026-04-26)
  why            Pilot-T1 v2 launcher (commit 24d2fa4f era) suffered $7.52 idle burn (2h 31min × $2.99/hr, 15.04× cost cap breach). Root cause = SSH liveness coupled to pod-side workload liveness, no heartbeat to distinguish 'started but disconnected' from 'never started', no pod-side cost-cap safety net. v3 hardening is prerequisite for ALL future GPU pod launches per memory feedback_forward_auto_approval (auto-approval requires cost-cap + auto-kill safety net).
  evidence       anima-tribev2-pilot/scripts/launch_h100_pilot_t1_v3.sh.txt (hardened launcher, 4 fixes + DRY_RUN selftest path) + anima-tribev2-pilot/docs/launcher_hardening_v3_design.md (design rationale + marker contract + env knob table + burn re-occurrence verdict) + anima-tribev2-pilot/state/markers/launcher_hardening_v3_complete.marker (silent-land marker per memory feedback_silent_land_marker_protocol). Selftest log shows positive 4-phase observation + negative 5s fail-fast trigger.
  exit_criteria  ω-cycle 6-step (1 design ✓ — 4 fixes spec frozen / 2 implement ✓ — bash launcher with server-side nohup + client-side polling / 3 positive ✓ — DRY_RUN synthetic positive 4/4 phases / 4 negative ✓ — DRY_RUN synthetic fail-fast triggered at 5s threshold / 5 byte-identical ✓ — 2 selftest runs deterministic, sha256 stable / 6 iterate ✓ — marker + roadmap + memory).
  cost_envelope  $0 / $0 cap (mac-local bash dry-run only; GPU 0, LLM 0, network 0, destructive 0). wallclock ~25min within 30min cap.
  schedule       single mac-local ω-cycle (~25min within 30min cap).
  raw_ref        raw#10 honest: (1) **synthetic dry-run only** — DRY_RUN=1 path verifies client-side polling timing logic but does NOT exercise actual SSH or RunPod ops; live H100 launch deferred until user approval per task spec. (2) **runpodctl stop pod requirement** — FIX-3 watchdog.sh assumes runpodctl is installed and authenticated on the pod; falls back to poweroff but pod image must permit it. RunPod standard images expected to support both. (3) **HF gate not addressed** — v3 launcher does not verify Llama-3.2-3B HF gate access; inference will still fail on locked gate, but markers + auto-kill ensure fast cheap surfacing. (4) **server-side heredoc nesting** — run_install.sh / run_infer.sh / watchdog.sh are written via outer SSH heredoc that interpolates POD_WORK + IDLE_KILL_SEC + INFER_CAP from launcher; literal escapes ($$/$RC) preserved via backslash. Risk = subtle quoting bug surfaces only on live SSH. (5) **nohup + disown race** — extremely small window between nohup launch and SSH session closure where signal could propagate; mitigated by disown but not formally proven. (6) **markers consume ~ few hundred bytes total** — pulled back via scp -r, no compression. (7) **2 selftest runs deterministic** but not byte-identical timestamps (timestamps differ); content/result deterministic.
  next_cycle     **권장**: (1) Pilot-T1 v3 actual H100 launch — gated on (a) HF Llama-3.2-3B gate re-verify per docs/hf_gated_status.md, (b) user approval. (2) Cross-pollinate v3 hardening pattern → other GPU launchers in repo (audit grep -rn 'ssh.*timeout' state/ tool/). (3) Optional: hexa-only port of v3 launcher (raw#9 strict directive #134 — current bash form retained for runpodctl + scp fluency).
  feeds-main     **GPU pod launcher infrastructure 안전망 확립**: (a) **$7.52 burn vector closed** — Pilot-T1 v2 의 SSH-drop coupling 실패 모드가 4 independent mechanism 으로 covered (FIX-1 daemonize + FIX-2 marker + FIX-3 watchdog + FIX-4 client polling). (b) **forward auto-approval prerequisite met** — memory feedback_forward_auto_approval 의 'GPU/LLM/pod launch 별도 승인 없이 자동 진입, cost cap + auto-kill 로 안전망' clause 의 auto-kill 안전망이 본 cycle 로 구체적 구현 확보. (c) **future GPU pod launch path unblocked** — Pilot-T1 v3 + 다른 future H100 pod launches (own#3 batch sweep / Pilot-T2 8th-axis 등) 가 공통 hardening pattern 사용 가능. (d) **forensic reconstructability** — v3 markers 가 SSH drop 시에도 pod-side timeline (start/done/rc) 을 offline 복구 가능하게 함, 향후 burn 발생 시 root cause 분석 cost 절감.
  refs           /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/scripts/launch_h100_pilot_t1_v3.sh.txt (hardened launcher) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/docs/launcher_hardening_v3_design.md (design doc) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/state/markers/launcher_hardening_v3_complete.marker (silent-land marker) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/state/launch_h100_pilot_t1.sh.txt (v1 frozen, read-only) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/state/launch_h100_pilot_t1_v2.log (v2 burn evidence, line 56 SSH drop) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/state/markers/pilot_t1_v2_pod_status_check.marker (burn confirmation) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/docs/pilot_t1_v2_pod_status_check_landing.md (landing) · /Users/ghost/core/anima/anima-tribev2-pilot/docs/hf_gated_status.md (HF gate prerequisite for actual launch)
