roadmap 243 done "[CMT scale-saturation bug fix — axis 100 follow-up to #237 — anima_cmt_v2.hexa MLP-only sub-module ablation pre-registered, in-vivo retest DEFERRED] **Root cause analysis** (#237 12B+ rel=1.000 SATURATED uninformative): v1 helper tool/anima_cmt.hexa registers register_forward_hook on entire transformer block (layer) via zero_hook → Y_abl ≈ 0 in residual stream at scale → rel = ||Y_full - Y_abl|| / ||Y_full|| degenerates to unity regardless of family axis. **HCSF hypothesis pre-registration**: HCSF-A SCALE_NORM (magnitude renormalization sufficient — REJECTED a-priori, normalization cannot fix Y_abl≈0) / HCSF-B HID_DIM_BOUND (architecture-level fix needed — LIKELY) / HCSF-C ARTIFACT_OF_HYBRID (gemma hybrid attention sole cause — REJECTED, Mistral-Nemo non-hybrid also fully saturates). **Verdict pre-in-vivo-retest = HCSF-B_HID_DIM_BOUND_LIKELY**. **Fix design** (tool/anima_cmt_v2.hexa, 14177B, 232L hexa raw#9, sha=fc42dc964dcf2292, chflags uchg locked, byte-identical 2-run helper sha=cee75d63a121b118 180L Python ast_parse=ok): (change 1) hook registered on layer.mlp instead of layer — preserves attention residual path, decouples ablation magnitude from total residual norm, restores informative rel ∈ (0,1); (change 2) scale-invariant norm_dy = abs/sqrt(h_dim) added alongside abs/rel for cross-scale comparability when h_dim varies (4096→5120→3584); (change 3) saturation_frac diagnostic in summary (count of cells with rel>=0.99), gate now requires informative=True (sat_frac<0.5) AND dominant rel>=0.05; (change 4) ANIMA_ABLATE_TARGET=layer env fallback to v1 behavior for A/B comparison; (change 5) MLP submodule discovery covers Mistral/Qwen2-3/Llama/gemma-2 naming (mlp/feed_forward/ffn/feedforward/feed_forward_layer). **Disk evidence consolidation** (state/cmt_scale_saturation_fix/{baseline_7b,patched_12b}/cmt_results.json + summary_fix.json): 7B v1-regime baseline (mistral-7B-v0.3 / qwen3-8B / llama-3.1-8B / gemma-2-9b) all sat_frac=0.0 informative=True (rel mean 0.016-0.030 — under-saturated direction, dominant rel still meaningful) / 12B+ v1-regime patched evidence (Mistral-Nemo-12B + qwen3-14b + gemma-2-9b at Phase 3a) shows Mistral-Nemo sat_frac=1.0 + gemma sat_frac=1.0 fully saturated, qwen3-14B sat_frac=0.0 informative — confirming bug is backbone-conditional NOT pure scale (Qwen3-14B at 14B remains informative under v1 regime). **In-vivo retest STATUS=PRE_REGISTERED_DEFERRED**: v2 helper validated mac-local (selftest PASS, hexa parse OK, helper Python ast_parse=ok, byte-identical 2× re-emit). GPU re-launch blocked by (a) $0.50 cap insufficient for 5-bb full re-run (~$0.50-0.85 estimated), (b) Llama-3.1-70B HF gated unblock pending axis 86, (c) multi-session parallel Claude commit hygiene per memory project_parallel_claude_sessions. Pre-registered Phase 3a-followup retest plan: 5-bb (Mistral-7B + Mistral-Nemo-12B + Qwen3-8B + Qwen3-14B + gemma-2-9b) × ANIMA_ABLATE_TARGET=mlp default, validate (i) 12B+ saturation_frac drops <0.5, (ii) 7B baseline stays informative + dominant_rel preserved, (iii) per-family dominant layer surfaces (compare to v1 regime for Qwen3-14B as control). **raw#10 honest 5 caveats**: (1) N=2 12B+ sample (Mistral-Nemo + gemma) for saturation hypothesis — generalize cautiously to other 12B+ architectures (Qwen3-14B already disconfirms pure scale → backbone-conditional); (2) Qwen3-14B at v1 was already informative — suggests 12B alone is not sufficient cause, RoPE/SwiGLU/QK-norm/RMSNorm variants may matter; (3) MLP-only ablation is one of several possible fixes (attention-only, residual-path-partial, layer-norm-disabled would also work and may give different tomography); (4) pre-registered v2 helper has not been validated in vivo — analysis-only verdict pending GPU retest; (5) rel_distribution.std/mean is the proper saturation discriminator; saturation_frac<0.5 is conservative threshold (50% threshold may need tightening to 0.3 or 0.1 once in-vivo data is back). **ω-cycle 6-step PASS**: (R1 design — HCSF-A/B/C frozen + 4-bb v1-regime baseline disk evidence consolidated) (R2 implement — anima_cmt_v2.hexa raw#9 strict 232L hexa native, MLP-only hook + scale-invariant norm_dy + saturation diagnostic + env fallback, hexa parse OK + Python ast_parse=ok + byte-identical 2× helper sha cee75d63) (R3 positive — selftest emits helper OK; 7B v1 baseline confirms informative regime; 12B+ v1 evidence confirms saturation pattern) (R4 negative — Qwen3-14B v1 informative disconfirms pure scale → HCSF-C rejected, refines hypothesis to backbone-conditional) (R5 byte-identical — helper sha + hexa source sha frozen + chflags uchg lock applied) (R6 land — summary_fix.json + per-bucket cmt_results.json + marker state/_marker_axis106_cmt_fix_1777222738.flag + memory project_cmt_scale_saturation_fix + roadmap 243 + commit). **constraints honored**: mac-local + GPU 0 + LLM 0 + network 0 + destructive 0 + cost $0 / cap $0.50 (GPU optional bypassed due to multi-session hygiene + 5-bb scope > cap). raw#9 strict (hexa native 232L + emitted helper Python only as raw#37 transient). raw#15 SSOT (axis 100 helper as canonical source, in-place edit avoided to preserve v1 lineage for Mk.XII Phase 3a artifact reproducibility). 한글 200자 보고."
